vulnerability.name: USN-5734-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that FreeRDP incorrectly handled certain data lenghts. A malicious server could use this issue to cause FreeRDP clients to crash, resulting in a denial of service, or possibly obtain sensitive information. This issue only affected Ubuntu 18.04 LTS, Ubuntu 20.04 LTS, and Ubuntu 22.04 LTS. (CVE-2022-39282, CVE-2022-39283)  It was discovered that FreeRDP incorrectly handled certain data lenghts. A malicious server could use this issue to cause FreeRDP clients to crash, resulting in a denial of service, or possibly obtain sensitive information. (CVE-2022-39316, CVE-2022-39317, CVE-2022-39318, CVE-2022-39319, CVE-2022-39320)  It was discovered that FreeRDP incorrectly handled certain path checks. A malicious server could use this issue to cause FreeRDP clients to read files outside of the shared directory. (CVE-2022-39347)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in FreeRDP.
